    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Police Custody Suite - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_police_custody_suite">Police Custody Suite</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_justice_organisation">Justice Organisation</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_police_custody_suite">Police Custody Suite</xref>
 is a designated area within a police station or other building, where people are held having been apprehended by the police and prior to being remanded by the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_court">Courts</xref>
 or released.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on Health and Justice healthcare, see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/health-just/"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Health and Justice</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
